  What is man, when you come to think upon him, but a minutely set, ingenious machine for turning with infinite artfulness, the red wine of Shiraz into urine?

  &mdash; Isak Dinesen 

  Red wine with fish. Well, that should have told me something.

  &mdash; Bond in From Russia with Love (1963)

  I rather like bad wine . . . one gets so bored with good wine.
  
  &mdash; Benjamin Disraeli, Earl of Beaconsfield 1804 - 1881

  I have eaten your bread and salt.
  I have drunk your water and wine.
  The deaths ye died I have watched beside
  And the lives ye led were mine.
  
  &mdash; Rudyard Kipling 1865 - 1936

  Who does not love wine, women, and song
  Remains a fool his whole life long.
  
  &mdash; Johann Heinrich Voss 1751 - 1826

  Some of the most dreadful mischiefs that afflict mankind proceed from wine; it is the cause of disease, quarrels, sedition, idleness, aversion to labor, and every species of domestic disorder.

  &mdash; François de Salignac de la Mothe Fénelon 1651 - 1715

  The wine urges me on, the bewitching wine, which sets even a wise man to singing and to laughing gently and rouses him up to dance and brings forth words which were better unspoken.
  
  &mdash; Homer, "The Odyssey"